From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karel Nagel <nagelkarel@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Apr 2026 14:45:00 +0000
Subject: arm64: dts: qcom: qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a: add venus encoder SID

The upstream Venus DT node only maps SID 0x2180 (controller/MVSC).
The vcodec core (MVS0) DMA uses SID 0x2184, which causes SMMU
translation faults and crashes during video encoding. Add the
missing stream ID so both controller and core DMA are mapped.

Signed-off-by: Karel Nagel <nagelkarel@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a.dts | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a.dts
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs6490-radxa-dragon-q6a.dts
@@ -1335,6 +1335,8 @@

 &venus {
 	status = "okay";
+	iommus = <&apps_smmu 0x2180 0x20>,
+		 <&apps_smmu 0x2184 0x20>;
 };

 /* PINCTRL - additions to nodes defined in sc7280.dtsi */
